# Vercel Speed Insights Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for this Next.js project.

## What Was Implemented

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/speed-insights@2.0.0` using pnpm
- Updated package.json with the new dependency
- Updated pnpm-lock.yaml to ensure consistent dependency resolution

### 2. Code Changes
Modified `/app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the root layout's body, placed alongside the existing `<Analytics />` component

## Implementation Details

Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart), I implemented the framework-specific instructions for Next.js 13.5+ using the App Router:

1. **Framework Detection**: Identified this as a Next.js 16.0.10 project using the App Router
2. **Package Manager**: Detected pnpm as the project's package manager based on existing pnpm-lock.yaml
3. **Installation**: Used `pnpm add @vercel/speed-insights` to install the latest version (2.0.0)
4. **Integration**: Added the SpeedInsights component to the root layout following Next.js App Router best practices
5. **Placement**: Positioned the component at the end of the body tag, consistent with the existing Analytics component pattern

## Verification

✓ Build completed successfully with `pnpm build`
✓ No TypeScript compilation errors
✓ All static pages generated correctly
✓ Package dependencies installed and locked

## Files Modified

- `/app/layout.tsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component
- `/package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `/pnpm-lock.yaml` - Updated lock file with new dependency tree

## Next Steps

To start collecting Speed Insights data:
1. Enable Speed Insights in your Vercel project dashboard
2. Deploy the application to Vercel
3. After users visit your site, performance metrics will be available in the Vercel dashboard

## Notes

- The SpeedInsights component follows the same pattern as the existing Analytics component
- No breaking changes were made to existing functionality
- The implementation preserves all existing code structure and patterns
- Pre-existing ESLint configuration issue was noted but is unrelated to this implementation
